| `getPostsChunkAroundPost` | `mattermost-redux/selectors/entities/posts` (memoized factory) |
| `getUnreadPostsChunk` | `mattermost-redux/selectors/entities/posts` |
| `getRecentPostsChunkInChannel` | `mattermost-redux/selectors/entities/posts` |

### Step 2 — Extract the ordered post ID array (lines 76–80)
```ts
if (chunk) {
    postIds = chunk.order;      // ← This is the raw string[] of post IDs
    atLatestPost = Boolean(chunk.recent);
    atOldestPost = Boolean(chunk.oldest);
}
```

`chunk.order` is the `string[]` field of a `PostOrderBlock` — the Redux-stored, ordered list of post IDs for that chunk.

### Step 3 — Assign to `postListIds` in the returned props (line ~96)
```ts
return {
    // ...
    postListIds: postIds,   // ← directly passed as the postListIds prop
    formattedPostIds,       // ← a further-processed version passed separately
    // ...
};
```

### Summary
> **`postListIds` = `chunk.order`**, where `chunk` is a `PostOrderBlock` object read from the Redux store via one of three selectors (`getPostsChunkAroundPost`, `getUnreadPostsChunk`, or `getRecentPostsChunkInChannel`), chosen based on whether the view is a permalink, an unread anchor, or the default recent-posts view. The raw `.order` array (an ordered list of post ID strings, newest-first) is assigned directly to `postListIds` in `mapStateToProps` inside **`components/post_view/post_list/index.tsx`**.

